Interview Question

What is a variable in Python?

Answer

A variable is a container used to store data values. Python does not require declaring the variable type explicitly because it is dynamically typed.

Example
# variables.py

# integer
age = 21

# string
name = "Sharan"

# float
price = 99.99

print(age)
print(name)
print(price)
Interview Tip

Python automatically determines the type of variable.
